    <stitle>T 444E Diesel Engine Diagnostics (1997) - SECTION 3.5: CIRCUIT FUNCTION AND DIAGNOSTICS - CRUISE CONTROL,
        PTO, HAND THROTTLE SYSTEM - RPS DIAGNOSTICS
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="0">
        <title>RPS DIAGNOSTICS</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>The ECM monitors the R-APS signal input at ECM terminal 30 from the remote pedal sensor for
                out-of-range signals, high or low.
            </para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>FLASH CODE 213 - ATA CODE SID 29 FMI 4 - ECM: RPS ORL</title>
            <para>If the ECM detects a RPS signal lower than 152 mV, this code is set and the remote pedal is
                disabled.
            </para>
            <para>CORRECTIVE ACTION: Perform Testing RPS Circuits (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk document="e125_384.xml" xrefid="ef12518147">3.154</hotlnk>
                    and
                    <hotlnk document="e125_384.xml" xrefid="ef12518148">3.155</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ).
            </para>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>FLASH CODE 214 - ATA CODE SID 29 FMI 3 - ECM: RPS ORH</title>
            <para>If the ECM detects a RPS signal greater than 4.55 volts, this code is set and the remote pedal is
                disabled.
            </para>
            <para>CORRECTIVE ACTION: Perform Testing RPS Circuits (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk document="e125_384.xml" xrefid="ef12518147">3.154</hotlnk>
                    and
                    <hotlnk document="e125_384.xml" xrefid="ef12518148">3.155</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                )
                <emph type="bold">.</emph>
            </para>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
